      "writtenOn": "2021-01-07T14:10:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I assume that a follow-up will support constant folding of \u0027!true\u0027, but it seems odd to include this function in this CL, when it always fails, then returns the wrong thing? Maybe leave it out so the base-class ABORT is triggered instead?",
