        "id": 11059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-07T14:32:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is triggering the ABORT the right thing? I considered it a bad thing to trigger an ABORT when we could reasonably continue compiling a program. If we somehow fold down an expression to `-true`, yes it indicates that we failed to type-check something somewhere, but is that worth crashing Chrome versus just returning `true`? SkDEBUGFAIL seemed like a better option to me--we\u0027d get signal that we missed a typecheck somewhere (the fuzzer will catch it), but in the wild we\u0027d continue compiling and get a reasonable final program.",
      "parentUuid": "250ed544_c6dd61ad",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 99,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 102,
        "endChar": 0
